qas.question: During the period from 1989 - 1996, what was the total are of the US in miles?
According to the CIA World Factbook, what is the total area of the US in miles?
According to the Encyclopedia Britannica, what is the total area of the US in miles?
The total square miles of land only in the United States was 9,372,610 km² during what time period?
Currently the World encyclopedia mileage of the United States is what?
What encyclopedia includes both the Great Lakes and coastal waters in the United States square mileage?
These sources consider overseas territories all fifty states and what?

context: From <b3_0>1989 through 1996,<b3_0/> the total area of the US was listed as 9,372,610 km2 (<a0_0>3,618,780 sq mi<a0_0/>) (land + inland water only). The listed total area changed to 9,629,091 km2 (3,717,813 sq mi) in 1997 (Great Lakes area and coastal waters added), to 9,631,418 km2 (3,718,711 sq mi) in 2004, to 9,631,420 km2 (3,718,710 sq mi) in 2006, and to 9,826,630 km2 (3,794,080 sq mi) in 2007 (territorial waters added). Currently, the CIA World Factbook gives <b4_0>9,826,675 km2<b4_0/> (<a1_0>3,794,100 sq mi<a1_0/>), the United Nations Statistics Division gives 9,629,091 km2 (3,717,813 sq mi), and the <b5_0>Encyclopædia Britannica<b5_0/> gives 9,522,055 km2 (<a2_0>3,676,486 sq mi<a2_0/>)(Great Lakes area included but not coastal waters). These source consider only the 50 states and <b6_0>the Federal District<b6_0/>, and exclude overseas territories.
